Note:
==============================================================================
RSA - RFC 8017 / PKCS#1 v2.2 implementation
==============================================================================

Implements the full PKCS#1 v2.2 (RFC 8017) suite:

Primitives (section 5):
  RSAEP  - RSA encryption  : c = m^e mod n
  RSADP  - RSA decryption  : m = c^d mod n   (with blinding)
  RSASP1 - signature       : s = m^d mod n   (with blinding)
  RSAVP1 - verification    : m = s^e mod n

Encoding (section 9):
  EMSA-PSS         - PSS encode/decode      (section 9.1)
  EMSA-PKCS1-v1_5  - legacy encode          (section 9.2)
  EME-OAEP         - OAEP encrypt/decrypt   (section 7.1)
  EME-PKCS1-v1_5   - legacy encrypt/decrypt (section 7.2)

Schemes (sections 7 and 8):
  RSAES-OAEP             - encryption (recommended)
  RSAES-PKCS1-v1_5       - legacy encryption
  RSASSA-PSS             - signature (recommended)
  RSASSA-PKCS1-v1_5      - legacy signature

Mask generation: MGF1 (section B.2.1) parametrized on SHA-256 / SHA-384 /
SHA-512 from sha2.runa.

Key layout: every key value is a BigInt allocated from the caller's arena.
The public key is (n, e); the private key holds (n, d, p, q, dp, dq, qInv)
for CRT-accelerated signing.

Constant-time / side-channel resistance:
- Every private-key operation uses RSA BLINDING: input m is masked by a
  random r^e mod n before the modexp, then unmasked by r^-1 mod n after.
  This randomizes the value the modexp operates on so timing or power
  analysis of the modexp inner loop cannot recover d. Kocher 1996.
- The modexp itself is bigint_mod_exp which walks the exponent bit-by-bit
  (not constant-time over the exponent value, but the input is blinded so
  the value seen by the modexp is random per call).
- OAEP decryption uses constant-time byte comparison via secure_memory to
  prevent Manger's attack (chosen-ciphertext padding-oracle CRYPTO 2001).
- PKCS#1 v1.5 paths document the Bleichenbacher CRYPTO 1998 risk and the
  caller is responsible for treating decryption failures uniformly.

References:
- RFC 8017 "PKCS #1: RSA Cryptography Specifications Version 2.2".
- Kocher "Timing Attacks on Implementations of Diffie-Hellman, RSA, DSS,
  and Other Systems" (CRYPTO 1996).
- Bleichenbacher "Chosen Ciphertext Attacks Against Protocols Based on
  the RSA Encryption Standard PKCS#1" (CRYPTO 1998).
- Manger "A Chosen Ciphertext Attack on RSA Optimal Asymmetric Encryption
  Padding (OAEP)" (CRYPTO 2001).
- Bellare, Rogaway "Optimal Asymmetric Encryption" (Eurocrypt 1994).
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "runtime/core/memory/arena.runa" as Arena
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/bigint.runa" as BigInt
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/bigint_extra.runa" as BigIntX
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/sha2.runa" as Sha2
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/entropy.runa" as Entropy
Import "compiler/frontend/import_system/crypto/secure_memory.runa" as SecureMem

Constant RSA_HASH_SHA256 as Integer is 0
Constant RSA_HASH_SHA384 as Integer is 1
Constant RSA_HASH_SHA512 as Integer is 2
Note: Sentinel ids for hash algorithms that are syntactically representable
Note: in legacy RSA parameter encodings (RFC 4055 §3.1 mandates SHA-1 as the
Note: PSS DEFAULT) but are NOT cryptographically acceptable for verification
Note: in this implementation. The parsing surface (rsa_decode_pss_parameters)
Note: returns these ids when the corresponding hash OID is encountered or
Note: when the RFC 4055 absent-field default applies; the strength gate in
Note: the verifier (rsa_public_set_hash and the PSS verify dispatch) MUST
Note: reject any signature whose effective hash id is RSA_HASH_SHA1 or
Note: RSA_HASH_MD5 with verify=0. Slot numbers chosen to be disjoint from
Note: the accepted SHA-2 slots (0..2).
Constant RSA_HASH_SHA1 as Integer is 100
Constant RSA_HASH_MD5  as Integer is 101

Note: Key struct layout (40 bytes for public, 96 bytes for private):
Note:   public: { n_ptr, e_ptr, modulus_bits, modulus_bytes, hash_alg }
Note:   private: { n_ptr, e_ptr, d_ptr, modulus_bits, modulus_bytes,
Note:              hash_alg, p_ptr, q_ptr, dp_ptr, dq_ptr, qInv_ptr }

Constant RSA_PUBLIC_KEY_BYTES as Integer is 40
Constant RSA_PRIVATE_KEY_BYTES as Integer is 96

Process called "rsa_hash_output_size" takes hash_id as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns the digest size in bytes for the named hash.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    SHA-256 -> 32, SHA-384 -> 48, SHA-512 -> 64.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Single comparison.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Public dispatch.
    @End Security_Scope

    If hash_id is equal to RSA_HASH_SHA256:
        Return 32
    End If
    If hash_id is equal to RSA_HASH_SHA384:
        Return 48
    End If
    If hash_id is equal to RSA_HASH_SHA512:
        Return 64
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "rsa_hash" takes arena as Integer, hash_id as Integer, msg as Integer, msg_length as Integer, out_digest as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Dispatches to the SHA-2 variant identified by hash_id.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Selects sha256_hash / sha384_hash / sha512_hash.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Cost is that of the underlying hash.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Public dispatch.
    @End Security_Scope

    If hash_id is equal to RSA_HASH_SHA256:
        Return proc sha256_hash from Sha2 with arena, msg, msg_length, out_digest
    End If
    If hash_id is equal to RSA_HASH_SHA384:
        Return proc sha384_hash from Sha2 with arena, msg, msg_length, out_digest
    End If
    If hash_id is equal to RSA_HASH_SHA512:
        Return proc sha512_hash from Sha2 with arena, msg, msg_length, out_digest
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Key struct accessors (public)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "rsa_public_key_alloc" takes arena as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Allocates an empty public-key struct.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    arena_allocate 40 zeroed bytes.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Single arena allocation.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    No side-channel.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let key be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, RSA_PUBLIC_KEY_BYTES
    If key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than RSA_PUBLIC_KEY_BYTES:
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with key, i, 0
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return key
End Process

Process called "rsa_public_set_n" takes key as Integer, n as Integer returns Integer:
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with key, 0, n
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "rsa_public_set_e" takes key as Integer, e as Integer returns Integer:
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with key, 8, e
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "rsa_public_set_bits" takes key as Integer, bits as Integer returns Integer:
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with key, 16, bits
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with key, 24, bits divided by 8
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "rsa_public_set_hash" takes key as Integer, hash_id as Integer returns Integer:
    proc memory_set_qword from Memory with key, 32, hash_id
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "rsa_public_get_n" takes key as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc memory_get_qword from Memory with key, 0
End Process

Process called "rsa_public_get_e" takes key as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc memory_get_qword from Memory with key, 8
End Process

Process called "rsa_public_get_bits" takes key as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc memory_get_qword from Memory with key, 16
End Process

Process called "rsa_public_get_modulus_bytes" takes key as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc memory_get_qword from Memory with key, 24
End Process

Process called "rsa_public_get_hash" takes key as Integer returns Integer:
    Return proc memory_get_qword from Memory with key, 32
End Process

