Process called "rsa_private_key_alloc" takes arena as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Allocates an empty private-key struct.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    arena_allocate 96 zeroed bytes.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Single arena allocation.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    No side-channel.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let key be proc arena_allocate from Arena with arena, RSA_PRIVATE_KEY_BYTES
    If key is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than RSA_PRIVATE_KEY_BYTES:
        proc memory_set_byte from Memory with key, i, 0
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return key
End Process

